Segmentation:

The synthetic rubber called Ethylene Propylene Diene Monomer (EPDM) is an elastomer with a diverse variety of uses. Because EPDM has several distinctive qualities, like good weather resistance, heat resistance, and vibration absorption, it may be used in a variety of automotive applications. It is often used in automotive parts such hoses, weather-stripping, brake parts, windshield wipers, body sealing, tubing, radiator, belts, engine mounts, roofing membrane, weather-stripping, thermoplastic vulcanizates, and applications for motor oil additives. Additionally, it is utilised in mechanical items for under-the-hood uses. The rising demand for synthetic rubber in the construction and automotive sectors is one of the key factors driving this industry. In addition, the market for EPDM is probably being driven by rising building activity.

